<topic id='attribute_tnm_version_number.description'>
  <title>Description</title>
  <titlealts>
    <searchtitle>Attribute: TNM VERSION NUMBER - Description</searchtitle>
  </titlealts>
  <body>
  <div>
      <p>
The 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_tumour">Tumour</xref>, Node and Metastasis version number in use during a 
              <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
               keyref="business_definition_cancer_care_spell">Cancer Care Spell</xref>.        </p>
      <p>
         <xref outputclass="attribute" keyref="attribute_tnm_version_number">TNM VERSION NUMBER</xref>
 is either the:        </p>
      <ul>
         <li>
            <div>
               <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                     keyref="business_definition_american_joint_committee_on_cancer">American Joint Committee on Cancer</xref>
               <p>
 (<xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_american_joint_committee_on_cancer">AJCC</xref>), 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_union_for_international_cancer_control">Union for International Cancer Control</xref>
 (<xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_union_for_international_cancer_control">UICC</xref>) or 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_european_neuroendocrine_tumor_society">European Neuroendocrine Tumor Society</xref>
 (<xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_european_neuroendocrine_tumor_society">ENETS</xref>) version number used for 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_tumour">Tumour</xref>, Node and Metastasis (TNM) staging for cancer diagnosis or                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
Pathological 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_union_for_international_cancer_control">Union for International Cancer Control</xref>
 (<xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_union_for_international_cancer_control">UICC</xref>) version number used for Tumour, Node and Metastasis (TNM) staging for cancer diagnosis.                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
      </ul>
      <p>Note:</p>
      <ul>
         <li>
            <div>
               <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_tumour">Tumour</xref>
               <p>
(T) describes the size of the 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition" keyref="business_definition_tumour">Tumour</xref>
 and whether it has invaded nearby 
                                <xref outputclass="class" keyref="class_tissue">TISSUE</xref>
               </p>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>
Node (N) describes regional 
                                <xref outputclass="businessDefinition"
                        keyref="business_definition_lymph_node">Lymph Nodes</xref>
 that are involved                    </p>
            </div>
         </li>
         <li>
            <div>
               <p>Metastasis (M) describes distant metastasis (spread of cancer from one body part to another).</p>
            </div>
         </li>
      </ul>
  </div>
</body>
